/span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/01 12:21:57 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Lava Walker drops Blizzard?</span><hr size=1> Can any of you confirm/deny that the Lava Walker in SF drops the spell Blizzard?<br>
 <p><img src="http://www.xmission.com/~nimphe/NimpheSig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/01 12:26:32 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lava Walker drops Blizzard?</span><hr size=1> Yes.  Any of the mobs on the named cycle in Skyfire can drop Blizzard.  Even though you specifically referred to the Lava Walker, I assume you know about the named cycle, right?<br>
<br>
Druid spells I've personally found on named cycle mobs: Blizzard, Form of Howler, Fist of Karana (several copies), Breath of Karana, Frost, Girdle of Karana.<br>
<br>
The nice thing is that you can solo nearly all of the named cycle mobs except for two: Eldrig and the shadow drake.  The latter usually summons, but not always.  People have reported LWs summoning, but I've never run into a summoning LW yet.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufibtastormwillow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Fibta Stormwillow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/6/01 1:03:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lava Walker drops Blizzard?</span><hr size=1> I have in fact run into a lavawalker that summoned.  I didn't like it much. <br>
<br>
Fibta Stormwillow, 59 Druid, Quellious <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukhieran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khieran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 3:39:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lava Walker drops Blizzard?</span><hr size=1> I've killed Lava Walker a lot with a necro friend - he seems to summon about 10% of the time<br>
<br>
No Blizzard for me yet though from all the nameds I've killed :( <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukatlynel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Katlynel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/01 9:25:02 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.asianavenue.com/indiegrrl/faedrake.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lava Walker drops Blizzard?</span><hr size=1> Lava Walker summoned me two days ago.  Ouchie.  Luckily I was able to channel a gate. <p><font face="Verdana, Arial" size="2">
Katlynel Wolfcaller
<BR>56 Preserver, <a href="http://www.aradani.com/warcouncil">The War Council</a>, Saryrn
</font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=felessan>Felessan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/8/01 5:11:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lava Walker drops Blizzard?</span><hr size=1> Lava walker 0wnZ me :P<br>
<br>
I've run across him once when he didn't summon, managed to solo him (just) at 51.<br>
<br>
Since then he's killed me at least 3 or 4.<br>
<br>
He'll pay.  OH he will pay. &gt;D <p>Felessan<BR>
Wood-elf wanderer of the Fourth Wall<br>
Tarew Marr</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaelwr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aelwr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/9/01 4:41:16 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lava Walker drops Blizzard?</span><hr size=1>  I killed it 3 times and got a bit overconfident. I was root dotting it and got summoned couldn't channel gate and was killed. After I ran back he was still rooted right over my corpse. Fortunately a group nearby pulled him off so that I could loot my corpse.<br>
<br>
Aelwr 56th Druid<br>
Innoruuk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=shaielofbrell>ShaielofBrell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/10/01 8:36:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The LavaWalker is bad bad bad</span><hr size=1> I have run into him twice- both summoners.<br>
<br>
Shaiel<br>
Preserver of 59 unimplemented quests <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukobara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kobara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/10/01 1:15:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lava Walker drops Blizzard?</span><hr size=1> Aelwr, you found him rooted over body? You should be aware that no mobs in the zone EXCEPT Talendor and Guardian Wurms can see thru Camo... I have died many times for a bad pull/adds that I have just gone invis and dragged to BW zone safely with no trouble.<br>
<br>
I finally got a copy of Blizzard off  a Soul Devourer near BW zone yesterday. Nice spell at times (if not resisted, and if soloing) It will affect not only the Mob, but also you if you are too close or run into the AE as it is hitting. Resists seem to run 1 out of the 3 waves, but of course is level dependent and MR dependent. <p>Kobara Wyndryder <BR>
59 Preserver, <BR>
Officer & Druid-Elder <BR>
Alliance of the Night,Tribunal</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urhesolooshun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhes Olooshun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/12/01 1:08:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lava Walker drops Blizzard?</span><hr size=1> I, personally, ended my Blizzard hunt this weekend, finally getting it to drop off of a Faerie of Dismay in Skyfire.  I hunted in that zone for nearly ALL of my lvl 54 xp and dinged to 55 shortly after that kill.  It seems to be one of the rarer druid drops, ranking up there with Girdle of Karana and Breath of Karana .<br>
<br>
And as far as the Lava Walker summoning goes, there seems to be a level range on these ranging from 48-52 with the lvl 51-52 being summoners.  I usually pull em to the BW zone and root them near the zone line, cast a winged death on em and wait for root to break.  If they summon, I high tail it to the BW zone, if not, I kill em.  <br>
<br>
